        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Time::Str - Time Zones and Leap Seconds]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[Time::Str parses and formats date/time strings across 20+ standard formats, with an optional C/XS backend and nanosecond precision. The previous post, Introducing Time::Str, covered parsing and formatting. This one covers two additions, time zones and leap seconds, and ends with a note on the new C parsers. (<a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/perl/comments/1u4qkgr/timestr_time_zones_and_leap_seconds/">Reddit</a>)]]></description>
            <pubDate>2026.06.10</pubDate>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://blogs.perl.org/users/chansen/2026/06/timestr---time-zones-and-leap-seconds.html</guid>
            <link>https://blogs.perl.org/users/chansen/2026/06/timestr---time-zones-and-leap-seconds.html</link>
            
            
            
